article.headline: (25) HOUSTON 75, WICHITA ST 61
article.story:
WICHITA, Kansas (Ticker) -- Chandi Jones scored 21 points to 
lead No. 25 Houston to a 75-61 victory over Wichita State.

The Lady Cougars took a 42-30 lead into the break after shooting
56 percent (19-for-34) from the field in the first half.

Joann Overstreet netted 10 of her 16 points in the second half
and Sancho Lyttle recorded 15 points and seven rebounds for
Houston (13-2), which has won eight straight games.

Reserve center Kiemona Harris chipped in 12 points and five
rebounds for the Lady Cougars, who are off to their best start
since 1991-92 when they opened at 14-1.

Houston was outrebounded, 43-34, but scored 35 points off of 32
turnovers by the Shockers.

Tisharria Huggins netted 17 points and Angela Buckner produced
13 points and 13 boards for Wichita State (4-8), which led,
10-2, in the opening minutes before allowing a 30-10 run by the
Lady Cougars.
